'''BID 610''' or '''Alvis''' was a British [[cipher machine]] used by both [[United Kingdom|British]] and [[Canada|Canadian]] governments.<ref name=aldrich-bd610>{{cite book|last=Aldrich|first=Richard|title=GCHQ|publisher=[[Harper Press]]|year=2010|page=210|isbn=9780007312665}}</ref><ref name=jproc-bd610>{{cite web|title=BID 610 (Alvis)|url=http://www.jproc.ca/crypto/bid610.html}}</ref> It was the first fully transistorised full-duplex online cipher machine used by the British Army.<ref name=jproc-bd610/> It was introduced in the 1960s.<ref name=aldrich-bd610/><ref name=jproc-bd610/>

